Name of this JSP implies its always read-only. This is not the case. Its made read only by the thing that paints it setting it to be read only:

pdWid.setReadOnly(true);

Rename this widget to remove the &quot;readonly&quot;.

Mocktio doesnt support mocking of static methods, so we need to use JMockit for this purpose -&gt; ProxyRetriever.getProxy(caseBusinessEntity, OCCaseForAbsence.class);
However, (currently) JMockit fails in eclipse when you return a BO from a method such as absenceCaseEntity.getBusinessEntity(), hence we just mockito for this.

I agree its confusing, but its currently not possible to use just one mocking library AND have the test run eclipse. If it doesnt run in eclipse, its annoying as you must run the all the tests, which is slow. There is a JIRA for the JMockit issue: http://jira/browse/FDP-1594

