I&#39;m gessing we&#39;re creating a new object because the service doesn&#39;t get injected in a multilayer usage.

Can&#39;t we use a method to retrieve the instance that already exists instead of creating a new one?

Something like:

	private CsvLoadDataService getCsvLoadDataService() {
		if (csvLoadDataService == null) {
			csvLoadDataService = (CsvLoadDataService) InstanceManager.getInstance().getInstance(CsvLoadDataService.class);
		}
		return csvLoadDataService;
	}


This can later be removed when the @Inject is fixed and works properly.


I think this a cleaner way to get the service. Instead of having two instances of CsvLoadDataService we only have one.

